<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870703-0179 </DOCNO><HL> Hudson Bay Mining Project</HL><DD> 07/03/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> HBM.S IRCMINING, METALS (NON-PRECIOUS) (MIN) </IN><DATELINE> TORONTO  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Hudson Bay Mining andamp; Smelting Co. and Outokumpu Mines Ltd. said they plan to develop a mine at their Namew Lake nickel property in northern Manitoba.    Adrian Molinari, president of Outokumpu Mines, a unit of Outokumpu Oy of Finland, said development costs would be about 70 million Canadian dollars ($52.6 million).    Hudson Bay, a unit of Inspiration Resources Corp., New York, has a 60% interest in the mine and Outokumpu, 40%.    The companies said production is scheduled to begin in the fourth quarter of 1988 at an annual rate of 68,000 tons of nickel concentrate and 13,500 tons of copper concentrate. The mine has proven reserves of 2.8 million tons grading 2.44% nickel and 0.9% copper. </TEXT></DOC>